What you need to know:  Kenya collected 37 medals--24 gold, 10 silver and three bronze--to top in the two-day championships that attracted six countriesIt’s the glamour girls Mercy Chepkemei, Peninah Mutisya and Judy Kemunto, who swept all the podium places in women’s under-20 1,500m final to wrap up the last day in style for KenyaEvans Kipkosgei swept through the red tartan track in 13:51.02 to win boys’ under-18 5,000m gold, beating compatriot Brian Muange to second place in 13:55.56